<br>
The elders of the pack have revised the guild initiation procedure.  We haven't decided against the voting in procedure, but currently it is not working as intended.  Mostly, it is taking too long to approve a cub (over 2 weeks).  To alleviate this, we are adopting the following procedure:<br>
<br>
(1) All people wanting to join the Aegis Wolves on Tunare shall post (or have posted for them) an request to join on the Tunare Cubs board.  The request should contain pertinant character details (race, class, level) at a minimum.<br>
<br>
(2) Any member of the Pack who has reason to object to the application shall post that objection on the same thread as the application.  An elder will investigate the objection and attempt to resolve any negative issues.  If the issue is resolved, he will post that fact (and any information which should be public) on the application thread.<br>
<br>
(3) Four elders will interview the applicant (in irc, game chat or in-game).  Once they have interviewed the applicant and approve of the application, they will either (a) post that affirmation on the application thread on these boards or (b) notify the guild secretary (Forin Ironshield) via e-mail (ForinIronshield@Yahoo.com) and he will post the affirmation.<br>
<br>
(4) Once the four interviews and affirmations are completed, and provided that there are no unresolved negative issues, the cub will be tagged and assigned a mentor.<br>
<br>
(5) The mentor will be responsible for (a) conveying pack history and rules to the cub and (b) introducing the cub to as many wolves as possible during the cubs mentoring/probation period.<br>
<br>
(6) The mentoring/probation period shall be two weeks.  During that time, the cub may be removed by a majority vote of a quorum of the elders.  Any improper action by the cub should be conveyed to an officer as soon as possible.<br>
<br>
(7) At the end of the mentoring/probation period, the cub will be given a quest for advancement to pup rank.<br>
<br>
